sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Pveg-spoVG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter Pveg and RBS spoVG for B. subtilis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Constitutive promoter veg(<bbpart>BBa_K143012</bbpart>) coupled to the strong Ribosome Binding Site spoVG(<bbpart>BBa_K143021</bbpart>) from ''B. subtilis''.
Pveg-spoVG can be used in the context of a '''Ribosomes per second''' (RiPS) output generator
'''To get the highest level of translation from this Promoter-RBS combination it must be connected to a coding region preceded by a coding region prefix<cite>1</cite>. A standard prefix will increase the distance between the RBS and the start codon, reducing translational efficiency.'''
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris Hirst
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Pveg-spoVG was synthesised by GeneArt
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence of Pveg was obtained from the DBTBS<cite>1</cite> and RBS-spoVG were obtained from papers<cite>2</cite> and the sequence synthesised by GeneArt

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RBS-spoVG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: SpoVG ribosome binding site (RBS) for B. subtilis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Description: SpoVG is an endogenous ribosome binding site from B.subtilis. The sequence of the spoVG ribosome binding site is AAAGGUGGUGA which is complementary to the sequence UUUCCUCCACU from the 3' region of the 16s rRNA from B.subtilis. Previous research showed that the predicted binding energy of the 16s rRNA to the RBS is -19kcal <cite>1</cite>
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: James Chappell
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was taken from a previous research paper [1] and was constructed by Geneart.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to ensure that the RBS is functional the actual ribosome binding site was maintained and the distance between the RBS and the start codon maintained. In order to conform to the biobrick standard the sequence flanking the RBS had to be changed but the distance between the promoter and RBS, and start codon and RBS was maintained.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Pveg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter veg a constitutive promoter for B. subtilis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Pveg is a constitutive promoter that constitutively expresses the P43 protein in ''B.subtilis''. Pveg contains binding sites for the ''B.sutbilis'' major sigma factor<cite>#1</cite>. Pveg in ''B.subtilis'' utilises two binding sites to cause high expression of genes<cite>#2</cite>, however our Pveg is lacking the upstream site to give a medium level of gene expression. It has been noted that the sporulation master regulatoion factor spoOA interacts with Pveg though it is not known how<cite>#3</cite>. The context with which we used the promoter Pveg is as a '''Polymerase Per Second''' (PoPS) generator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: James Chappell
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Pveg promoter was suggested to us by Dr. Jan-Willem Veening of Newcastle University. This sequence supplied was compared to that of the DBTBS database<cite>#3</cite> then a section containing the binding site synthesised by Geneart.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The biobrick part was designed to include a single binding site for the ''B.subtilis major sigma factor. In addition the biobrick standard was applied to the promoter Pveg sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI 434
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cI repressor from phage 434 (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The 434 cI repressor protein coding sequence is a 710 base-pair sequence with the standard RBS-compatible BioBrick prefix and the standard BioBrick suffix sections on its ends. sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: TE from coliphageT7
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
